If the PTEs aren't unmapped, they *remain PRESENT*. If they remain present, subsequent accesses from the reader threads to the unpunched pages *DO NOT PAGE FAULT!* And no page fault means `filemap_get_entry()` is *NOT CALLED*! Okay, now I have to check `split_huge_pmd_locked` in `mm/huge_memory.c` to confirm my understanding.


